						<summary>

						<p>Slab in front of the Bhairava temple on the Bhairavakoṇḍa hill.</p>						

						<p>Dēvarāya Oḍeya I, 1402 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1324, Chitrabhānu, Āshāḍha ba. 3 Sunday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1402 A.D. June 18, Sunday.</hi></p>						

						<p>States that Bommi Reḍḍi, son of Siṅgāya reḍḍi of Donakoṇḍa, renovated the temple of Nīlakaṇṭhadēva on the Udayagiri hill in Ēṟuva-nāḍu for the merit of his father and mother Chevasāni.</p>						

						</summary>
